defs.docs: Programmers can have a little vec, as a treat.

defs.name: Array
defs.docs: A trait for types that are an array.

defs.name: Item
defs.docs: The type of the items in the thing.

defs.name: CAPACITY
defs.docs: The number of slots in the thing.

defs.name: as_slice
defs.docs: Gives a shared slice over the whole thing.

defs.name: as_slice_mut
defs.docs: Gives a unique slice over the whole thing.

defs.name: ArrayVec
defs.docs: An array-backed, vector-like data structure.

defs.name: append
defs.docs: Move all values from `other` into this vec.

defs.docs: A `*mut` pointer to the backing array.

defs.docs: Performs a `deref_mut`, into unique slice form.

defs.name: as_ptr
defs.docs: A `*const` pointer to the backing array.

defs.docs: Performs a `deref`, into shared slice form.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: The capacity of the `ArrayVec`.

defs.name: clear

Creates a draining iterator that removes the specified range in the vector
 and yields the removed items.

Inserts an item at the position given, moving all following elements +1
 index.

defs.docs: Checks if the length is 0.

defs.docs: The length of the `ArrayVec` (in elements).

defs.docs: Remove and return the last element of the vec, if there is one.

defs.name: push

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Removes the item at `index`, shifting all others down by one index.

defs.docs: Forces the length of the vector to `new_len`.

defs.docs: Fill the vector until its capacity has been reached.

defs.name: split_off
defs.docs: Splits the collection at the point given.

defs.name: swap_remove

defs.name: truncate
